SECTION 5: m_tau PREDICTED FROM K = 2/3 EXACTLY
----------------------------------------------------------------------

  IF K = 2/3 exactly:
    sum_m / (sum_sqrt)^2 = 2/3
    (sum_sqrt)^2 = (3/2) * sum_m

  Let s = sqrt(m_e) + sqrt(m_mu), x = sqrt(m_tau).
  Let S = m_e + m_mu.
  Then: (s + x)^2 = (3/2) * (S + x^2)
    s^2 + 2sx + x^2 = (3/2)S + (3/2)x^2
    s^2 + 2sx - (1/2)x^2 = (3/2)S
    x^2 - 4sx + (3S - 2s^2) = 0  [multiply by -2]

    s = sqrt(m_e) + sqrt(m_mu) (MeV^1/2)   10.993867906
    S = m_e + m_mu (MeV)                   106.16937445
    s^2 (MeV)                              120.86513153

    Quadratic c = 3S - 2s^2 (MeV)          76.777860298
    Discriminant = 16s^2 - 4c (MeV)        1626.7306632
    sqrt(disc) (MeV^1/2)                   40.332749265

    x_+ (MeV^1/2)                          42.154110444
